Mrs. Gore founded Tennessee Voices for Children to support young people with serious behavioral, emotional, substance abuse, or other mental health problems. Mrs. Gore received her Bachelor’s degree in Psychology from Boston University in 1970 and her Master’s degree in Psychology from George Peabody College in 1975. Mrs. Gore worked as a photographer for the Nashville Tennessean until Vice President Gore was elected to Congress in 1976.

>mask on
meant to be a self-insert and not an established character. the "character" of Anon could be anyone. for lower-detail or sketch-type art where you don't have to put in a ton of time, it's a great way to focus on the female anthro rather than the human male. the mask or featureless human face also looks out of place if it's a high-quality piece.
>mask off
an established character with a recognizable face. make him the default male character settings from any video game and it will be easy for people here to self-insert. add distinguishing features and he'll be his own man.
